Renoir: Life and Works
Sourcebooks | 2000 | ISBN: 1570716927 | English | 148 pages | PDF | 17.3 MB

RIERRE-AUGUSTE RENOIR (1841-1919) favorite among the Impressionists, Renoir depicted the sweetness of life of everyday events -of couples dancing, parties lunching, street scenes of shoppers. Follow Renoir's development from an apprentice painter of porcelain to the consummate master of large-scale figurative paintings
